\par\b\fs32 SchoolCRM – Full Detailed Documentation\b0\fs22\par
\par
\par\b\fs28 1. Project Overview\b0\fs22\par
\par SchoolCRM is a role-based school management system built with PHP, MySQL, Bootstrap, and shared frontend assets. It supports three core personas:
\par\tab\bullet\tab **Student**: views attendance, marks, homework, notifications, timetable, fee info.
\par\tab\bullet\tab **Teacher**: records attendance, publishes homework and announcements, updates marks.
\par\tab\bullet\tab **Admin**: governs users, academic operations, approvals, permissions, analytics, planning.
\par
\par------------------------------------------------------------\par
\par
\par\b\fs28 2. Architecture and Folder Responsibilities\b0\fs22\par
\par
\par\b\fs24 2.1 Entry and compatibility layer\b0\fs22\par
\par\tab\bullet\tab `index.php` — common login UI.
\par\tab\bullet\tab Root compatibility wrappers (e.g., `adminDashboard.php`, `FeeDetails.php`) keep older links working and delegate to `modules/...`.
\par
\par\b\fs24 2.2 Role modules\b0\fs22\par
\par\tab\bullet\tab `student/` — student-first pages and role-specific workflows.
\par\tab\bullet\tab `teacher/` — teacher-first pages and data-entry workflows.
\par\tab\bullet\tab `admin/` — admin governance + operations pages.
\par
\par\b\fs24 2.3 Shared/cross-cutting\b0\fs22\par
\par\tab\bullet\tab `backoffice/` — login, logout, password/session paths and legacy aliases.
\par\tab\bullet\tab `forms/` — submission and AJAX endpoints.
\par\tab\bullet\tab `config/` — database wiring.
\par\tab\bullet\tab `middleware/` — access checks.
\par\tab\bullet\tab `assets/` — CSS/JS/vendor dependencies.
\par\tab\bullet\tab `modules/` — reorganized legacy page implementations grouped by domain.
\par
\par------------------------------------------------------------\par
\par
\par\b\fs28 3. Authentication and Session Flow\b0\fs22\par
\par
\par\b\fs28 3.1 Login flow\b0\fs22\par
\par 1. User opens `index.php`.
\par 2. Submits username, password, and role.
\par 3. `backoffice/login.php` validates credentials against `user_login`.
\par 4. On success, session variables are set (`access`, `name`, `id`).
\par 5. Redirect target depends on role:
\par    - student → student dashboard route
\par    - teacher → `teacher/dashboard.php`
\par    - admin → `admin/dashboard.php`
\par
\par\b\fs28 3.2 Legacy admin route compatibility\b0\fs22\par
\par To support older bookmarks/redirects, these compatibility entrypoints exist:
\par\tab\bullet\tab `backoffice/adminDashBoard.php`
\par\tab\bullet\tab `backoffice/adminDashboard.php`
\par
\par Both load `admin/dashboard.php`.
